To find an equation, let C represent the cost of the rental, and use t for the number of hours:
        \text{Cost}\amp=(\$5\text{ insurance fee})+(\$3\text{ per hour})\times\text{(number of hours)}
        C\amp=5+3\cdot t=8

An equation for the concentration of toxic chemicals is C=285-15t To find the C-intercept, set t equal to zero. 

            C=285-15(0)=285
            The C-intercept is the point (0, 285), or simply 285.  To find the t-intercept, set C equal to zero and solve for t.


                \begin{align*}
                \alert{0}=285-15t \text{Add }15t \text{ to both sides.}
                15t=285  \text{Divide both sides by 15.}
                t=19    
                \end{align*}


        The t-intercept is the point (19,0), or simply 19.

\begin{align*}
150x-18(\alert{0})=9000 \text{Simpify.}
150x=9000  \text{Divide both sides by 150.}
x=60    
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
150(\alert{0})-18y=9000 \text{Simpify.}
-180y=9000  \text{Divide both sides by } -180\text{.}
y=-50    
\end{align*}
